# [NTP](../wg/ntp.html)

## Summary
The NTP working group met at IETF 125 to discuss the status of core protocol developments, security extensions, and new individual submissions. A significant portion of the meeting was dedicated to administrative updates, including a change in Area Directors, and status reports on `draft-ietf-ntp-ntpv5` and `draft-ietf-ntp-nts-for-ptp`. The group also reviewed a proposal for hardware-rooted attestation for PTP and coordinated with IEEE 1588 activities.

## Key Discussion Points

### Administrative and AD Change
*   **Area Director Transition:** Eric Vyncke is stepping down as the long-serving Area Director. Tommy Jensen is the incoming AD for the NTP working group. 
*   **Document Status:** 
    *   The PTP for NTP document is currently in the RFC Editor queue.
    *   The Roughtime document (`draft-ietf-ntp-roughtime`) has passed IESG balloting and authors are working to clear the final "Discuss" positions.

### Working Group Documents
*   **NTPv5 (`draft-ietf-ntp-ntpv5`):**
    *   Miroslav Lichvar (via the mailing list) identified four remaining issues. 
    *   The chairs requested more reviews as the document is maturing.
    *   A virtual interim meeting and a Hackathon project in Vienna are planned to progress this work.
*   **NTS for PTP (`draft-ietf-ntp-nts-for-ptp`):**
    *   Martin Langer reported that the draft is nearing completion.
    *   Current gaps include finishing the Security and IANA Considerations sections.
    *   The draft is being aligned with ongoing developments in the IEEE 1588 security subcommittee.
    *   Martin Langer and Ryan Brzozowski intend to finalize the draft and integrate changes into implementations for testing later this year.
*   **NTS for NTP Pools:**
    *   The working group has adopted the NTS for NTP Pools proposal as an experimental RFC. 
    *   The primary goal is to document the existing experiment. Future alternative proposals for NTS pools will be handled in separate documents.

### Individual Submissions
*   **NTPv5 Algorithms:** Sarah Grant and the chairs agreed that it is currently too early for this document. It will be allowed to expire and revisited once the base `draft-ietf-ntp-ntpv5` is further along.
*   **Timestamp Extension Field and DNS Record:** No significant progress reported since the last virtual interim; discussions on the DNS record document will continue on the mailing list.
*   **Hardware-Rooted Attestation for PTP:**
    *   Presented by Diego Lopez based on [Hardware-Rooted Attestation for PTP](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-ntp-hardware-rooted-attestation-for-ptp-00).
    *   The proposal focuses on using PTP to assess the physical location of servers (geofencing) and providing non-repudiation for PTP messages without impacting throughput.
    *   Technical mechanisms include using Trusted Platform Modules (TPM), Spiffy IDs for attestation, and Merkle trees to sign batches of messages (amortized execution). It also considers Post-Quantum Cryptography (PQC) readiness.
    *   Karen O'Donoghue and Eric Vyncke discussed the appropriate venue for this work, suggesting coordination with the RATS working group or the Security Area Advisory Group (SAG) to ensure connectivity with related IETF activities.

### IEEE 1588 Coordination
*   Work on Client-Server PTP (CSPT) continues within IEEE.
*   A current architectural blocker involves the decision between one-step and two-step clocks. 
*   Once resolved, updates will be rolled into the core specification, including NTS for CSPT.

## Decisions and Action Items
*   **`draft-grant-ntp-ntpv5-algorithms`:** Will be allowed to expire.
*   **NTS for NTP Pools:** Authors to submit the first working group version (-00) of the adopted draft.
*   **Attestation Proposal:** Diego Lopez to seek feedback from the IEEE 1588 security group and coordinate with Security ADs/SAG.

## Next Steps
*   **Virtual Interim:** To be scheduled between IETF 125 and IETF 126 (Vienna).
*   **IETF 126 Hackathon:** Plans are underway for Hackathon projects involving `draft-ietf-ntp-ntpv5` and NTS for PTP/CSPT.
*   **NTPv5 Review:** Working group members are encouraged to review the latest version of `draft-ietf-ntp-ntpv5` and comment on the four issues identified by Miroslav Lichvar on the mailing list.